main event: A round unidentified object was observed moving slowly across the sky and then disappeared in Abington, West Virginia in November 1957.
interesting points: The object was described as round with no lights or smoke,The observation lasted for about 30 seconds, The weather was clear at the time of the sighting, Multiple reports exist from different dates in November 1957 concerning sightings in Abington, Observers reported a high-speed maneuvering object that could not be identified.
witness description: Description from various observers but specific identities of witnesses were redacted or deleted.
